				"synopsis": {
					"type": 23,
					"value": "Parents are on the beach after the scene with the Druid Leader OR if the scene never happened for whatever reason. Locke's wife Marrick has either murdered Kagha, let her live or is sitting in the dark as others celebrate. Locke is  mainly concerned for his wife at this stage and the effects the events of the night have had on her. "
